<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="326" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,690,1291]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,690,715]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Description.</emphasis>
MALE. Length 
<number box="[491,508,691,715]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" value="4.0">4</number>
. mm. Head and mesosoma black, metasoma dark castaneous. Wings subhyaline. Clypeus with median lobe subtrapezoidal, lateral margin convex, apical margin slightly thick in frontal view, medially with boomerang-shaped polished area; median carina indistinguishable from surface, instead with sharp line. Frons strongly coriaceous, punctures little distinguishable from texture surface. Vertex slightly convex. Notaulus present on anterior half of mesoscutum. Scutellar disc strongly sharpened posteriorly, overlapping propodeal disc anteriorly, lateral border concave (
<figureCitation box="[703,771,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">
Fig. 
<number box="[755,771,870,895]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Propodeal disc with partially polished median depression, surrounded by sharp and high paramedian carina, median carina conspicuous and incomplete. Hypopygium (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,193,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[154,1433,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 22. Hypopygium, dorsal view; 10. Trichiscus suzannae; 11. T. wittei; 12. T. noorti sp. nov.; 13. T. denisi sp. nov.; 14. T. briani sp. nov.; 15. T. copelandi sp. nov.; 16. T. mourei sp. nov.; 17. T. lynnae sp. nov.; 18. T. normani sp. nov.; 19. T. luboi sp. nov.; 20. T. zuparkoi sp. nov.; 21. T. ohli sp. nov.; 22. T. camargoi sp. nov. (Scale bars = 50 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228359/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,942,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin conspicuously concave. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[867,1003,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[215,1364,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[215,1364,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 53. Male genitalia. 42 – 45 Trichiscus copelandi sp. nov.; 42. dorsal view; 43. ventral view; 44. lateral view; 45. ventral pair of aedeagal dorsal body, ventral view. 46 – 49 T. mourei sp. nov.; 46. dorsal view; 47. ventral view; 48. lateral view; 49. ventral pair of aedeagal dorsal body, ventral view. 50 – 53 T. lynnae sp. nov.; 50. dorsal view; 51. ventral view; 52. lateral view; 53. ventral pair of aedeagal dorsal body, ventral view. (Scale bars = 50 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228362/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">
Figs 
<number box="[928,1003,942,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" value="43.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="42.0">42–45</number>
</figureCitation>
). Basal parameral expansion conical. Basivolsella with spine-shaped median expansion, ventrad. Aedeagal ventral ramus very short, laminar, surface vertical, subrectangular in lateral view. Aedeagal dorsal body with three pairs of apical lobes, outer pair laminar, surface vertical, apex narrow and slightly ventrad in lateral view; ventral pair laminar, surface vertical and concave, apex with spine-shaped corners in lateral view, ventral one twisted and dorsal one straight; inner pair membranous, hairy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
